laboratory_examinations.findings: Lipase elevated to 150, which is above the normal range (Ref range: 94.0 - 250.0).

Small bilateral dependent pleural effusions noted; a 4 mm hypodensity within the right lobe of the liver likely represents a cyst; small amount of free perihepatic fluid and periportal edema observed; otherwise no focal liver lesions or abnormalities detected.
